The paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance on image classification tasks, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques for improving the network's out-of-sample performance, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of prior knowledge to extract superficial signals and the incorporation of the gray-level co-occurrence matrix (GLCM) suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper's focus on improving the network's ability to generalize to previously unseen domains suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of language processing techniques to describe the GLCM suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
